<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.35a.21.22.001" />
<fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
<note type="curatorial"></note>

<opener>
<address>
<addrLine>3305 20. 108
</addrLine>
<addrLine>Omaha 68144 Neb.
</addrLine>
</address>
<dateline>April 28, 1971
</dateline>
<salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
</opener>

<p>The finest program I've ever seen and heard on TV was Dick Cavett's last night. You were and are superb. My husband, children and grandchildren all loved it. I hope Channel 7 will do a</p>

<fw type="curatorial">22</fw>

<p>repeat of it soon.</p>
<p>I've always loved your poetry but I also love the way you give it your wisdom, your humanity, your strength, your sense of honor and common sense, your <unclear>closeness</unclear> to nature and to God- all of this and more- you breathed into your short one hour (minus commercials).</p>
<p>You have dwarfish anyone who has ever been on TV including Mr. Frost. </p>
<p>I hope you have done some recording on records that we may buy.</p>
<p>Thank you for a memorable evening. My nintey year old mother-in-law was thrilled, too.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Sincerely, </salute>
<signed>
Doris Pinkerton Madden</signed>
<note></note>
</closer>

</div1>
